                                jcr:lastModifiedBy="schafsm"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/container/v2/container">
                                <separator_copy
                                    cq:styleIds="[1662756423318]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-03-29T09:56:55.380-04:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-03-29T09:56:55.380-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/separator/v2/separator"/>
                                <text
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2022-12-24T15:16:38.383-05:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="schafsm"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2022-12-24T15:17:03.543-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="schafsm"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>Zuzek emphasizes that early intervention for spasticity is integral because after a stroke, the brain learns how to operate without the parts that were damaged by the stroke. But that can become more difficult over time. He says evidence supports early intervention as beneficial to early stages of brain plasticity, or the brain’s ability to change in response to experience or injury.&lt;sup>4&lt;/sup>&lt;/p>&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                                <separator_copy_518583648
                                    cq:styleIds="[1662756423318]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2023-03-29T09:56:55.380-04:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-03-29T09:56:55.380-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/separator/v2/separator"/>
                                <title
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1651545825694]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2022-12-24T15:17:16.740-05:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="schafsm"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2024-04-22T13:52:50.542-04:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    jcr:title="What’s next for Sophia"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/title/v2/title"
                                    type="h2"
                                    variant="h"/>
                                <text_1456326330
                                    cq:styleIds="[1659545825678]"
                                    jcr:created="{Date}2022-12-24T15:17:45.362-05:00"
                                    jcr:createdBy="schafsm"
                                    jcr:lastModified="{Date}2022-12-24T15:18:04.594-05:00"
                                    jcr:lastModifiedBy="schafsm"
                                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                    sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>A decade after her stroke, Sophia can walk, stand, wash her hair and dress herself – daily activities that were not possible before investing time in physical therapy and other strategies. And beyond day-to-day tasks, Sophia has done more than she ever imagined she could do, including continuing her love of travel with Joe.&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p>“We are having good lives at the moment,” Joe says. “I think we’ve been incredibly lucky that Sophia has come as far as she has.”&lt;/p>&#xa;"
                                    textIsRich="true"/>
                            </container_304918154>
